#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/portage-utils.xml:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/portage-utils.xml:37
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>portage-utils</c> is a collection of very fast utilities written in C, which\n"
"are meant to offer a faster but more limited alternative to their\n"
"<c>gentoolkit</c> counterparts. Please note that <c>portage-utils</c> is not\n"
"meant to replace <c>gentoolkit</c>. Its utilities are much more efficient than\n"
"the equivalent ones from <c>gentoolkit</c> and might be better suited to be\n"
"used in scripts that need to call Portage repeatedly, but <c>portage-utils</c>\n"
"does not offer the same functionalities. It does not consider eclasses at all\n"
"and does not provide tools like <c>revdep-rebuild</c> and <c>glsa-check</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/portage-utils.xml:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"More information about <c>gentoolkit</c> can be found in the <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/gentoolkit.xml\">Gentoolkit</uri> guide.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/portage-utils.xml:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can view the complete list of applications in <c>portage-utils</c> by typing\n"
"<c>man q</c> or <c>q --help</c>. Please read the man page for each utility\n"
"described, as this guide is only meant to be a short reference for the most\n"
"useful functions and does not include all the information about each\n"
"application.\n"
msgstr ""

