#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/portage-utils.xml:237
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extracting information from emerge logs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/portage-utils.xml:241
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There is also a tool that allows you to extract useful information from your\n"
"<path>emerge.log</path> file. It's called <c>qlop</c> and it can be useful when\n"
"you want to estimate package compilation times or compare with your friends\n"
"whose computer compiles faster. It also allows you to check what's compiling at\n"
"the moment and how long it will take - which is handy when you're working in the\n"
"console and don't have any other means to check it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/portage-utils.xml:249
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reading emerge logs with qlop"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/portage-utils.xml:250
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(I'm starting to emerge perl and I want an estimate on how long it usually takes)</comment>\n"
"$ <i>qlop -tH perl</i>\n"
"perl: 7 minutes, 52 seconds for 4 merges\n"
"<comment>(Now let's see what's emerging at the moment)</comment>\n"
"$ <i>qlop -c</i>\n"
"* perl-5.8.8-r23\n"
"    started: Mon May 21 12:41:11 2007\n"
"    elapsed: 19 seconds\n"
msgstr ""
